# React Frontend Standards

## Structure
- Pages in `web/src/pages/`; reusable UI in `web/src/components/{feature}/`
- API calls in `web/src/services/` — unwrap `ApiResponse<T>`, throw on missing `data`
- Types and `PERMISSIONS` in `web/src/types/index.ts`; mirror backend `RolePermissionMatrix` in `utils/permissions.ts`

## Data fetching
- Use React Query with org-scoped keys: `['pods', currentOrganization?.id]`
- Gate queries with `enabled: !!currentOrganization?.id && hasPermission(...)`
- Use `refetchInterval` for status pages; prefer SignalR (`usePodStatusHub`) for real-time pod updates

## Forms (reactstrap + react-hook-form)
- Use `innerRef={field.ref}` on reactstrap `Input` — not `{...register('field')}` alone
- Validate on submit; show toast errors via `react-toastify`
- Gate actions with `hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.*)` from `OrganizationContext`

## UX patterns
- Permission-denied → `<Alert color="warning">` early return
- Loading → `<Spinner />`; empty state with link to create flow
- Destructive actions (delete running pod) → confirmation modal with `force` flag

## API types
- Match backend Contracts field names (camelCase JSON): `gpuId`, `templateId`, `providerType`
- Use string union types for enums (`PodStatus`, `GpuType`, `ProviderType`)

## Scalability
- Keep components presentational; lift org/auth state to contexts
- Add new features as page + service + types + route in `App.tsx` + sidebar entry
- Do not import axios outside `services/api.ts`
